{{Infobox football biography | name = Isaac Success | image = | fullname = Isaac Success Ajayi<ref>{{cite web |title=Squads for 2016/17 Premier League confirmed |url= https://www.premierleague.com/news/84136 |publisher= Premier League |date=1 September 2016 |accessdate=11 September 2016}}</ref> | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1996|1|7|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Benin City]], Nigeria | height = {{height|m=1.82}} | currentclub = [[Watford F.C.|Watford]] | clubnumber = 10 | position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]] | youthyears1 = {{0|0000}}–2014| youthclubs1 = BJ Foundation | years1 = 2014–2015 | clubs1 = [[Granada CF B|Granada B]] | caps1 = 20 | goals1 = 9 | years2 = 2014–2016 | clubs2 = [[Granada CF|Granada]] | caps2 = 49 | goals2 = 7 | years3 = 2016– | clubs3 = [[Watford F.C.|Watford]] | caps3 = 42 | goals3 = 2 | years4 = 2018 | clubs4 = → [[Málaga CF|Málaga]] (loan) | caps4 = 9 | goals4 = 0 | nationalyears1 = 2013 | nationalteam1 = [[Nigeria national under-17 football team|Nigeria U17]] | nationalcaps1 = 7 | nationalgoals1 = 7 | nationalyears2 = 2015–2016 | nationalteam2 = [[Nigeria national under-20 football team|Nigeria U20]] | nationalcaps2 = 4 |nationalgoals2 = 2 | nationalyears3 = 2017– | nationalteam3 = [[Nigeria national football team|Nigeria]] | nationalcaps3 = 2 |nationalgoals3 = 0 | club-update = 08:26, 26 February 2019 (UTC) | ntupdate = 30 October 2018 }} '''Isaac Success Ajayi''' (born 7 January 1996) is a Nigerian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for English club [[Watford F.C.|Watford]] as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]].
==Club career== Success was born in [[Benin City]]. He started his career with local side BJ Foundation Academy appearing regularly for the side.<ref>[http://www.completesportsnigeria.mobi/readNewsItem1.php?nid=3891 Eaglets Striker Close To Udinese Deal]; Complete Sports Nigeria, 10 June 2013</ref>
In November 2013 Success agreed to a five-year deal with [[Udinese Calcio|Udinese]], starting January 2014,<ref>[http://allnigeriasoccer.com/read_news.php?nid=10942 Isaac Success Confirms He Will Join Udinese In January]; All Nigeria Soccer, 12 November 2013</ref> for a [[Euro|€]]400,000 fee.<ref>[http://www.tuttoudinese.it/calciomercato/isaac-success-la-nuova-scommessa-dell-udinese-7659 Isaac Success, la nuova scommessa dell'Udinese (Isaac Success, Udinese's new bet)]; Tutto Udinese, 26 May 2013 {{it icon}}</ref> However, he was only granted a work permit in March of the following year,<ref>[http://thenationonlineng.net/new/isaac-success-gets-work-permit-today/ Isaac Success gets work permit today]; The Nation Online, 14 March 2014</ref> and immediately joined [[Granada CF]], being assigned to [[Granada CF B|the reserves]] in [[Segunda División B]].<ref>[http://www.granadacf.es/es/el-club/noticias-club/671-success-isaac-y-uche-agbo-nuevos-jugadores-del-granada-cf Success Isaac y Uche Agbo: nuevos jugadores del Granada CF (Success Isaac and Uche Agbo: new player of Granada CF)] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140903053721/http://www.granadacf.es/es/el-club/noticias-club/671-success-isaac-y-uche-agbo-nuevos-jugadores-del-granada-cf |date=2014-09-03 }}; Granada's official website, 18 March 2014 {{es icon}}</ref>
On 31 August 2014 Success made his first-team debut, starting in a 1–1 away draw against [[Elche CF]] at the age of 18 years and seven months,<ref>[http://www.espnfc.com/spanish-primera-divisi%C3%B3n/match/402613/elche-granada/report Elche snatch last-gasp equalsier]; [[ESPN FC]], 31 August 2014</ref> being their youngest player ever to appear in a [[La Liga]] match.<ref>[http://www.marca.com/2014/09/01/futbol/equipos/granada/1409570467.html Success, jugador más joven en debutar en Primera con el Granada (Success, the youngest player to debut in ''Primera'' with Granada)]; [[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]], 1 September 2014 {{es icon}}</ref> He scored his first professional goal on 7 December, netting his side's only of a home draw against [[Valencia CF]], for the same scoreline.<ref>[http://www.espnfc.com/spanish-primera-division/match/402498/granada-valencia/report Granada 1–1 Valencia]; ESPN FC, 7 December 2014</ref> On 7 August 2015 Success extended his link with the club, signing until 2019 and being permanently promoted to the main squad.<ref>[http://granadacf.es/es/el-club/noticias-club/1515-isaac-success-ano-mas-de-contrato Isaac Success un año más de contrato (Isaac Success one more year of contract)]{{dead link|date=November 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}; Granada's official website, 7 August 2015 {{es icon}}</ref>
On 1 July 2016, Success agreed a five-year deal with [[Watford F.C.|Watford]] in a record transfer fee, estimated around £12.5&nbsp;million from Granada.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.watfordfc.com/news/article/2016-17/isaac-success-watford-fc-granada-premier-league-3160681.aspx|website=Watford F.C.|publisher=Club Journalist|accessdate=1 July 2016|title=Official: Isaac Success joins Watford FC}}</ref> Success scored once in 19 appearances in the 2016-17 season and, after just one appearance in 2017-18 was loaned to Malaga on 31 January 2018.<ref>[https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/42892598 Watford: Isaac Success joins Malaga on loan], BBC News, 31 January 2018</ref>
==International career== In 2013 Success was called up to [[Nigeria national under-17 football team|Nigeria under-17]]'s for [[2013 FIFA U-17 World Cup|the year]]'s [[FIFA U-17 World Cup]], being also named [[Captain (association football)|vice-captain]]. He appeared in the first two games, but was sidelined during the rest of the tournament due to an injury.<ref>[http://www.goal.com/en-sg/news/3955/africa/2013/11/08/4391901/isaac-success-fit-for-u-17-world-cup-final Isaac Success fit for U-17 World Cup final]; Goal.com, 8 November 2013</ref> Success got his first call up to the senior [[Nigeria national football team|Nigeria]] side for a [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] qualifier against [[Zambia national football team|Zambia]] in October 2016.<ref>{{cite news|title=Mikel Obi, Musa, Ikeme 20 others To battle Zambia |url=http://www.thenff.com/2016/09/6992/|accessdate=5 October 2016|publisher=thenff.com |date=22 September 2016}}</ref> On 23 March 2017, Success made his debut for Nigeria, coming on as a substitute in a 1–1 draw against [[Senegal national football team|Senegal]] at [[The Hive Stadium]] in [[London]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://goal.com/s/en/match/nigeria-vs-senegal/2413770|publisher=Goal|accessdate=24 March 2017|title=Nigeria 1 Senegal 1: Iheanacho earns a draw for Super Eagles}}</ref>
