{{Infobox football biography | name = Ken Sema | image = | fullname = Ken Nlata Sema | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1993|09|30|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Norrköping]], Sweden | height = {{height|m=1.80}} | position = [[Midfielder]] | currentclub = [[Watford F.C.|Watford]] | clubnumber = 12 | youthyears1 = {{0|0000}}–2013 | youthclubs1 = [[IFK Norrköping]] | years1 = 2013–2014 | clubs1 = [[IFK Norrköping]] | caps1 = 0 | goals1 = 0 | years2 = 2013 | clubs2 = → [[IF Sylvia]] (loan) | caps2 = 22 | goals2 = 4 | years3 = 2014–2015 | clubs3 = [[Ljungskile SK]] | caps3 = 60 | goals3 = 11 | years4 = 2016–2018 | clubs4 = [[Östersunds FK]] | caps4 = 58 | goals4 = 8 | years5 = 2018– | clubs5 = [[Watford F.C.|Watford]] | caps5 = 14 | goals5 = 1 | nationalyears1 = 2016 | nationalteam1 = [[Sweden national under-23 football team|Sweden U23]] | nationalcaps1 = 4 | nationalgoals1 = 1 | nationalyears2 = 2017– | nationalteam2 = [[Sweden national football team|Sweden]] | nationalcaps2 = 6 | nationalgoals2 = 0 | club-update = 08:35, 26 February 2019 (UTC) | nationalteam-update = 6 September 2018 }}
'''Ken Sema''' (born 30 September 1993) is a Swedish [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Watford F.C.|Watford]] as a [[midfielder]].
==Club career== ===Early career=== Sema got promoted to the [[IFK Norrköping]] first team as a 19-year old in 2013. However, he spent the entire season on loan to [[IF Sylvia]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nt.se/sport/nio-ifk-spelare-i-sylvias-trupp-8472975.aspx|title=Nio IFK-spelare i Sylvias trupp|first=Ulf|last=Stråhle|date=3 April 2013|publisher=}}</ref> and did not get his contract renewed after it expired at the end of the season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.expressen.se/sport/fotboll/sema-om-nobben-klart-jag-var-sur/|title=Sema om nobben: "Klart jag var sur"|publisher=}}</ref> In 2014, he signed for second tier team [[Ljungskile SK]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bohuslaningen.se/sport/fotboll/1.2842843-sema-och-bjorlund-klara|title=Sema och Björlund klara|publisher=}}</ref>
===Östersunds FK=== In January 2016, Sema signed for [[Östersunds FK]] in the [[Allsvenskan]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.op.se/fotboll/allsvenskan/ken-sema-bekraftar-overgangen-till-ofk-jag-ar-klar|title=Ken Sema bekräftar övergången till ÖFK: "Jag är klar"|publisher=}}</ref> where he would have his major breakthrough. Sema won the [[2016–17 Svenska Cupen]] with Östersund, assisting three of their four goals in the final,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aftonbladet.se/sportbladet/fotboll/a/1lByX/ostersund-vann-svenska-cupen|title=Östersund vann Svenska Cupen|publisher=}}</ref> and later played a major role in their [[2017–18 UEFA Europa League]] campaign. On 22 February 2018, Sema scored a goal in a 2–1 win against [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] in the round of 32. Despite this, Östersund were eliminated from the Europa League after losing 2–4 on aggregate.<ref>{{Cite web | title = Arsenal 1-2 Oestersunds FK - UEFA Europa League 2017/2018 Live | work = WhoScored.com | url = https://www.whoscored.com/Matches/1250853/Live/Europe-UEFA-Europa-League-2017-2018-Arsenal-Oestersunds-FK}}</ref>
===Watford=== On 4 July 2018, Östersunds FK chairman Daniel Kindberg revealed that Sema was close to signing for [[Premier League]] club [[Watford F.C.|Watford]] on a five-year contract.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.watfordobserver.co.uk/sport/16332898.watford-ostersund-confirm-ken-sema-transfer/|title=Ostersund confirm Sema's Watford switch|first=Harry| last=Gray|work=Watford Observer|date=4 July 2018}}</ref> The next day, Watford confirmed the signing.<ref>{{cite web|title=Official: Sema Signs On|url=https://www.watfordfc.com/teams/first-team/official-sema-signs|publisher=Watford F.C.|accessdate=5 July 2018}}</ref>
==International career== In 2016, Sema was a part of the [[Sweden national under-23 football team|Sweden Olympic team]] that played in Brazil, and scored his first U23 goal in a match against [[South Korea national under-23 football team|South Korea Olympic]]. In January 2017, he debuted for the [[Sweden national football team|Sweden senior team]] in a friendly 6–0 win over [[Slovakia national football team|Slovakia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com//football/match/2017/jan/12/sweden-v-slovakia|title=Sweden 6 - 0 Slovakia - Football|website=The Guardian}}</ref>
Sema was an unused substitute in [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA Second Round|the two-legged playoff]] against [[Italy national football team|Italy]] in November 2017, which Sweden won, and therefore qualified for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]]. Despite featuring in commercials with the rest of the Sweden squad before the World Cup, Sema was eventually left out of the World Cup squad.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aftonbladet.se/sportbladet/fotboll/a/xREJLj/sveriges-trupp-till-fotbolls-vm|title=Sveriges trupp till fotbolls-VM 2018 – här är alla som får åka till Ryssland|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.expressen.se/sport/fotbollsvm/jag-kan-forsta-att-det-blir-lite-skevt/|title=Märkliga Ica-bilderna: "Har blivit reaktioner"|publisher=}}</ref>
