{{Infobox football biography | name = Abdoulaye Doucouré | image = Stade rennais - Le Havre AC 20150708 40.JPG | caption = Doucouré in 2015 | fullname = Abdoulaye Doucouré<ref>{{cite web |title=Squads for 2016/17 Premier League confirmed |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/84136 |publisher=Premier League |date=1 September 2016 |accessdate=11 September 2016}}</ref> | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1993|1|1|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Meulan-en-Yvelines]], France | height = 1.82m | position = [[Midfielder#Central midfielder|Midfielder]] | currentclub = [[Watford F.C.|Watford]] | clubnumber = 16 | youthyears1 = 2004–2007 | youthclubs1 = OFC Les Mureaux | youthyears2 = 2007–2012 | youthclubs2 = [[Stade Rennais F.C.|Rennes]] | years1 = 2010–2013 | clubs1 = [[Stade Rennais F.C.|Rennes B]] | caps1 = 23 | goals1 = 2 | years2 = 2012–2016 | clubs2 = [[Stade Rennais F.C.|Rennes]] | caps2 = 75 | goals2 = 12 | years3 = 2016– | clubs3 = [[Watford F.C.|Watford]] | caps3 = 81 | goals3 = 11 | years5 = 2016 | clubs5 = → [[Granada CF|Granada]] (loan) | caps5 = 15 | goals5 = 0 | caps6 = 0 | goals6 = 0 | nationalyears1 = 2009–2010 | nationalteam1 = [[France national under-17 football team|France U17]] | nationalcaps1 = 19 | nationalgoals1 = 1 | nationalyears2 = 2010 | nationalteam2 = [[France national under-18 football team|France U18]] | nationalcaps2 = 5 | nationalgoals2 = 1 | nationalyears3 = 2011–2012 | nationalteam3 = [[France national under-19 football team|France U19]] | nationalcaps3 = 7 | nationalgoals3 = 0 | nationalyears4 = 2012–2013 | nationalteam4 = [[France national under-20 football team|France U20]] | nationalcaps4 = 3 | nationalgoals4 = 1 | nationalyears5 = 2014 | nationalteam5 = [[France national under-21 football team|France U21]] | nationalcaps5 = 1 | nationalgoals5 = 0 | club-update = 08:42, 26 February 2019 (UTC) | nationalteam-update = 13:25, 8 March 2014 (UTC) }}
'''Abdoulaye Doucouré''' (born 1 January 1993) is a French professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays for English club [[Watford F.C.|Watford]] as a [[Midfielder#Central midfielder|midfielder]].
==Club career== Doucouré was born in [[Meulan-en-Yvelines]], France, and is of [[Mali]]an descent and a practicing muslim. He made his debut in the [[Ligue 1]] during the 2012–2013 season. On 1 February 2016, Doucouré signed to [[Premier League]] side [[Watford F.C.|Watford]] for an undisclosed fee and immediately sent him to [[La Liga]] club [[Granada CF]] on loan.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/35465405|title=Watford sign Abdoulaye Doucoure and Adalberto Penaranda|publisher=BBC|date=1 February 2016|accessdate=2 February 2016}}</ref> Doucouré made his first La Liga appearance one week later, as he came on as an 80th-minute [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] for [[Adalberto Peñaranda]] in a 1–2 home loss against [[Real Madrid C.F.|Real Madrid]].<ref>http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-3436224/Granada-vs-Real-Madrid-La-Liga-LIVE-Cristiano-Ronaldo-company-look-close-gap-Barcelona-top.html</ref> Doucouré scored his first goal for Watford on 4 March 2017, netting an injury time consolation as Watford lost 3–4 to [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bbc.co.uk/sport/football/39086731|title=Watford 3–4 Southampton|publisher=BBC Sport|date=4 March 2017|accessdate=5 March 2017}}</ref>
Doucouré was awarded the 'Player of the Season' title for Watford at the end of the 2017–18 season.<ref>https://www.watfordfc.com/teams/first-team/end-season-awards-winners</ref>
