{{Spanish name|Navarro|Ceciliano}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Marc Navarro | image = | fullname = Marc Navarro Ceciliano | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1995|7|2|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Barcelona]], Spain | height = {{height|m=1.88}} | position = [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|Right back]] | currentclub = [[Watford F.C.|Watford]] | clubnumber = 23 | youthyears1 = 2001–2002 | youthclubs1 = [[CF Badalona|Badalona]] | youthyears2 = 2002–2011 | youthclubs2 = [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] | youthyears3 = 2011–2014 | youthclubs3 = [[RCD Espanyol|Espanyol]] | youthyears4 = 2013–2014 | youthclubs4 = → [[CF Damm|Damm]] (loan) | years1 = 2014–2017 | clubs1 = [[RCD Espanyol B|Espanyol B]] | caps1 = 44 | goals1 = 7 | years2 = 2017–2018 | clubs2 = [[RCD Espanyol|Espanyol]] | caps2 = 31 | goals2 = 3 | years3 = 2018– | clubs3 = [[Watford F.C.|Watford]] | caps3 = 1 | goals3 = 0 | nationalyears1 = | nationalteam1 = | nationalcaps1 = | nationalgoals1 = | club-update = 1 October 2018 | nationalteam-update = }} '''Marc Navarro Ceciliano''' (born 2 July 1995) is a Spanish professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for English club [[Watford F.C.|Watford]]. Mainly a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|right back]], he can also play as a [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|central defender]].
==Club career== ===Espanyol=== Born in [[Barcelona]], [[Catalonia]], Navarro finished his graduation on loan at [[CF Damm]], after representing [[CF Badalona]], [[FC Barcelona]] and [[RCD Espanyol]]. In July 2014, he was assigned to the latter's [[RCD Espanyol B|reserve team]] in [[Segunda División B]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lasegundab.es/blog/2014/07/10/el-espanyol-tira-de-la-cantera-29377.html|title=El Espanyol tira de la cantera|trans-title=Espanyol go shopping in the youth setup|publisher=La Segunda B|last=Tovar|first=Pedro|language=es|date=10 July 2014|accessdate=21 January 2017}}</ref>
Navarro made his senior debut on 2 November 2014, coming on as a second half [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] for [[Rober Correa]] in a 1–2 away loss against [[Elche CF Ilicitano]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.teleelx.es/n152625-El-Ilicitano-vence-al-Espanyol-B-con-trabajo-y-buen-futbol-2-1.html|title=El Ilicitano vence al Espanyol B con trabajo y buen fútbol (2–1)|trans-title=Ilicitano defeat Espanyol B with hard word and good football (2–1)|publisher=Tele Elx|language=es|date=2 November 2014|accessdate=21 January 2017}}</ref> His first goal came on 5 September of the following year, the winner in a 3–2 home success over [[FC Barcelona B]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mundodeportivo.com/futbol/fc-barcelona/20150905/201553398253/3-2-el-espanyol-b-lleva-de-cabeza-al-barca-b.html|title=3–2: El Espanyol B lleva de cabeza al Barça B|trans-title=3–2: Espanyol B get into Barça B's head|newspaper=[[Mundo Deportivo]]|last=Gascón|first=Javier|language=es|date=6 September 2015|accessdate=21 January 2017}}</ref>
On 22 December 2015, Navarro signed a one-year extension with the club, with his new contract running until June 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rcdespanyol.com/es/actualidad/_n:1857|title=Marc Navarro renueva una temporada|trans-title=Marc Navarro renews for one season|publisher=RCD Espanyol|language=es|date=22 December 2015|accessdate=21 January 2017}}</ref> The following 4 January, however, he suffered a severe [[knee]] injury, being sidelined for six months.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rcdespanyol.com/es/actualidad/grave-lesion-de-marc-navarro/_n:1934/|title=Grave lesión de Marc Navarro|trans-title=Serious injury of Marc Navarro|publisher=RCD Espanyol|language=es|date=4 January 2016|accessdate=21 January 2017}}</ref>
Navarro made his first-team – and [[La Liga]] – debut on 21 January 2017, starting and scoring the last goal in a 3–1 home win against [[Granada CF]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.marca.com/eventos/marcador/futbol/2016_17/la-liga/jornada_19/esp_gda/|title='Pericos' que vuelan|trans-title='Budgies' that fly|newspaper=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]|last=Pérez|first=José I.|language=es|date=21 January 2017|accessdate=21 January 2017}}</ref> and becoming the first youth graduate to achieve the feat since [[Raúl Tamudo]] in 1997.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sport.es/es/noticias/espanyol/espanyol-ahorrara-fichar-lateral-con-marc-navarro-5757373|title=El Espanyol se ahorrará fichar a un lateral con Marc Navarro|trans-title=Espanyol will save the signing of a full back with Marc Navarro|newspaper=[[Sport (Spanish newspaper)|Sport]]|last=Miguelsanz|first=Lluís|language=es|date=21 January 2017|accessdate=21 January 2017}}</ref> Eight days later, in his second appearance, he netted his team's second in a 3–1 defeat of [[Sevilla FC]] also at the [[RCDE Stadium]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.marca.com/laliga-fantasy/2017/01/29/588e2a1ee5fdeabd1c8b457e.html|title=El Espanyol tiene nuevo ídolo: Fantástico Marc Navarro|trans-title=Espanyol have a new idol: Fantastic Marc Navarro|newspaper=Marca|language=es|date=29 January 2017|accessdate=29 January 2018}}</ref>
On 30 January 2017, Navarro extended his contract until 2021, being definitely promoted to the first team [[2017–18 La Liga|the following campaign]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://futbol.as.com/futbol/2017/01/30/primera/1485777005_810078.html|title=El Espanyol renueva a Marc Navarro hasta 2021|trans-title=Espanyol renew Marc Navarro until 2021|newspaper=[[Diario AS]]|last=Molero|first=Iván|language=es|date=30 January 2017|accessdate=15 August 2017}}</ref>
===Watford=== On 15 June 2018, Navarro joined [[Watford F.C.|Watford]] on a five-year deal for €2 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rcdespanyol.com/ca/actualitat/_n:7395|title=Marc Navarro, al Watford|trans-title=Marc Navarro, to Watford|publisher=RCD Espanyol|language=ca|date=15 June 2018|accessdate=15 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.watfordfc.com/teams/first-team/official-navarro-joins-hornets|title=Official: Navarro joins Hornets|publisher=Watford F.C|date=15 June 2018|accessdate=15 June 2018}}</ref> His maiden [[Premier League]] appearance took place on 29 September, when played 84 minutes in the 0–2 away loss to [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/45610319|title=Arsenal 2–0 Watford|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|last=Chowdhury|first=Saj|date=29 September 2018|accessdate=2 October 2018}}</ref>
==Personal life== Navarro was a childhood friend of compatriot [[Héctor Bellerín]], who also played in England with Arsenal. The former commented that both used to play football together in the garden of his grandmother's house.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.mundodeportivo.com/futbol/premier-league/20181001/452120629323/hector-bellerin-marc-navarro-amistad-premier-league.html|title=De enfrentarse en el jardín de su abuela a hacerlo en la Premier League|trans-title=From facing each other in his grandmother's garden to doing so in the Premier League|newspaper=Mundo Deportivo|language=es|date=1 October 2018|accessdate=7 January 2019}}</ref>
